yprian. Migrated from Connecticut to the Ohio frontier — among the early settlers at Marietta, Washington County, in the Ohio Company's territory. EH #561 records his Ohio descendants at numbers 1494-1503."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Killed by a falling tree in Ohio, 1836","body":"He died in Ohio in 1836, killed by a falling tree. One son Norman had been killed earlier at Sandusky in 1813 during the War of 1812. EH numbers ten Ohio-born descendants in the next generation."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Fourteen years a magistrate of excellent judgment","body":"He served as a magistrate at Marion, Morgan County, Ohio for about fourteen years, and was generally accounted of good judgment and local influence. Both he and his wife Sarah were active church members from early life. The Hart Genealogy of 1875 records that the place was greatly missed and mourned over at his death, so great was the loss."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Andrews, Genealogical History of Deacon Stephen Hart (1875)","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Geneological_history_of_Deacon_Stephen_Hart_and_his_descendants%2C_1632._1875%2C_%28IA_geneologicalhist01andr%29.pdf"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"selah-hart-1767"},"I01254":{"id":"I01254","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Sarah","last_name":"Hart","maiden_name":"Walter","married_names":["Hart"],"extra_names":"EH #561 records maiden name as 'Walter'; the Hart Genealogy of 1875 records it as 'Waters'. Both forms attested.","gender":"female","display_name":"Sarah Walter Hart"},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1766,"month":3,"day":5},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":fa